creditline: Frederick R. Weisman Art Museum, University of Minnesota, on extended loan from the T. B. Walker Foundation
description: footed two-handled jar with slight taper at neck; decorated with pair of roosters on each side of body with lion under each handle; donkey flanked by two birds on one side of shoulder; lioness flanked by two human-headed birds on other side; incised details
title: Black-figure amphora
